WEBVTT
Kind: captions
Language: en

00:00:02.000 --> 00:00:03.380
<i>Narrator: Whenever
the president flies</i>

00:00:03.380 --> 00:00:04.750
<i>on an Air Force plane,</i>

00:00:04.750 --> 00:00:07.210
<i>its call sign is
Air Force One.</i>

00:00:07.210 --> 00:00:10.960
<i>But what if a president flies
on a commercial plane?</i>

00:00:10.960 --> 00:00:13.920
<i>What would air traffic control
call the plane</i>

00:00:13.920 --> 00:00:17.290
<i>flying the most important
passenger in the country?</i>

00:00:17.290 --> 00:00:20.420
- Well, President Richard Nixon
tried to do that.

00:00:20.420 --> 00:00:22.210
- We face the possibility

00:00:22.210 --> 00:00:25.250
of temporary fuel shortages
and some increases

00:00:25.250 --> 00:00:27.540
in fuel prices in America.

00:00:27.540 --> 00:00:30.420
<i>narrator: In the midst
of the 1973 energy crisis,</i>

00:00:30.420 --> 00:00:32.790
<i>with the cost of fuel spiking,</i>

00:00:32.790 --> 00:00:36.170
<i>Richard Nixon became
the first and only president</i>

00:00:36.170 --> 00:00:39.750
<i>ever to fly on
a commercial flight.</i>

00:00:39.750 --> 00:00:41.580
<i>- One of the things
Nixon was doing</i>

00:00:41.580 --> 00:00:45.120
<i>was trying to show that he
wasn't wasting gasoline,</i>

00:00:45.120 --> 00:00:47.830
<i>that he wasn't burning gas
for his vacation.</i>

00:00:47.830 --> 00:00:50.500
"I'm not one of these fat cats
spending money

00:00:50.500 --> 00:00:52.290
"when oil is so expensive

00:00:52.290 --> 00:00:54.750
and I'm riding on
the taxpayers' dime."

00:00:54.750 --> 00:00:57.170
<i>[whimsical music]</i>

00:00:57.170 --> 00:00:58.960
<i>narrator:
The day after Christmas,</i>

00:00:58.960 --> 00:01:00.710
<i>the Nixon family, his staff,</i>

00:01:00.710 --> 00:01:03.000
<i>and a dozen Secret Service
agents</i>

00:01:03.000 --> 00:01:05.580
<i>boarded United Airlines
Flight 55,</i>

00:01:05.580 --> 00:01:08.790
<i>a DC-10 from Washington
to Los Angeles.</i>

00:01:08.790 --> 00:01:11.670
<i>♪ ♪</i>

00:01:11.670 --> 00:01:15.000
<i>- The plane was then known
as "Executive One."</i>

00:01:15.000 --> 00:01:18.000
<i>That was its call sign
in air traffic control.</i>

00:01:18.000 --> 00:01:22.920
<i>♪ ♪</i>

00:01:22.920 --> 00:01:25.040
<i>narrator: According to press
reports at the time,</i>

00:01:25.040 --> 00:01:28.500
<i>flying "Executive One" saved
at least 60,000 gallons</i>

00:01:28.500 --> 00:01:30.620
<i>of jet fuel.</i>

00:01:30.620 --> 00:01:32.380
- If the energy crisis
continues,

00:01:32.380 --> 00:01:35.290
the President may find this
is the only way to fly.

00:01:35.290 --> 00:01:38.210
Ed Schumacher, ABC News
in Los Angeles.

00:01:38.210 --> 00:01:41.250
- What most of the American
public didn't realize was

00:01:41.250 --> 00:01:44.460
that Air Force One flew
to California

00:01:44.460 --> 00:01:46.540
empty anyway

00:01:46.540 --> 00:01:48.380
<i>to pick up President Nixon</i>

00:01:48.380 --> 00:01:50.460
<i>in California and bring him
back to Washington.</i>

00:01:50.460 --> 00:01:53.080
<i>And so the trip was entirely</i>

00:01:53.080 --> 00:01:54.460
<i>a photo op.</i>

00:01:54.460 --> 00:01:57.460
<i>[dramatic tone]</i>

